    <span class="name">Closing · where this brand is now</span>
    <span class="line"></span>
  </div>
  <h2 class="melis-section-title">Honest before impressive — including about the brand itself.</h2>

  <div class="melis-prose">
    <p>A brand book like this one risks reading as if everything is solved. It isn't. melis.ai is one operator's working theory of how a small AI-education brand should look, sound, and behave at this moment in the field — codified in detail because consistency at small scale needs more rigour than at large scale, not less.</p>
    <p>What's <em>true</em> here: the values, the stance, the visual language, the typography stack, the data-viz discipline, the tactile and cinematic libraries. These have all been tested in real work. They survive contact with shipping.</p>
    <p>What's <em>still settling</em>: the website rebuild is in flight. The Soul of the Machine newsletter has the look but the cadence is being established. The YouTube essay grammar is clear in description but the proof will come video by video. The sub-brand registry will move as products ship and others sunset. The component library expands as we hit new patterns.</p>
    <p>This document is the <em>spine</em>, not the finished body. If a future decision contradicts a rule in this book, the rule changes — and the change shows up here, with the date and a line on why. That's the contract. Living document, not stone tablet.</p>
  </div>

  <blockquote class="melis-quote">
    <p>"If a brand has to keep secrets to stay impressive, it's already over. This brand book is the first artefact that can't keep one."</p>
    <cite>— what this whole project is built around</cite>
  </blockquote>
</section>
